    <div class="main review-item" id="8280558">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/8280558/" class="title-link">世界不是平的</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-8280558"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/next99/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u1468427-5.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/next99/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">南萧亭</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2017-01-08"
      class="main-meta">2017-01-08 00:55:40</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_8280558_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  地图之所以令人感兴趣，主要来自两点： 首先，地图企图再现的世界本身不仅仅有无数的经纬坐标构成，而是有不同条件下各种便利和阻碍错综复杂的各种相互作用，这些作用导致各种条件下一次次“世界是平的”等预言先后落空。 其次，地图本身的技术手段必然会导致一定程度的变形或...

